        <title>Fixing Ctrl+Backtick in VSCode</title>
        <published>2023-06-25T00:00:00+00:00</published>
        <updated>2024-05-01T00:00:00+00:00</updated>
        <author>
          <name>Lan Lytt</name>
        </author>
        <link rel="alternate" href="https://lanlan.moe/blog/fix-vscode-ctrl-backquote/" type="text/html"/>
        <id>https://lanlan.moe/blog/fix-vscode-ctrl-backquote/</id>
        
        <summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;Yesterday, I encountered this &lt;a href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;github.com&#x2F;Microsoft&#x2F;vscode&#x2F;issues&#x2F;63659&quot;&gt;issue&lt;&#x2F;a&gt; while coding with Visual Studio Code. The default terminal shortcut &lt;code&gt;Ctrl+`&lt;&#x2F;code&gt; didn&#x27;t work on my new laptop. After some research, I learned that some CJK keyboards&#x2F;IMEs may reserve it for internal use, and the reserved key can still be used globally. So I tried to write a &lt;a href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;github.com&#x2F;lanlytt&#x2F;vscode-cjk-toggle-terminal-fixer&quot;&gt;fixer&lt;&#x2F;a&gt; to register it as a global hotkey and forward its keypress messages. Fortunately, it worked.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
</summary>
        
